<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Oil System Module Assembly and Secondary
        Filtration - Removal - Oil System Module
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="svcproc009" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Oil System Module</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                    safety instructions in the "Safety Information" section of this manual.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, make sure
                    the transmission is in neutral, parking brake is set, and wheels are blocked before doing diagnostic
                    or service procedures on engine or vehicle.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possibly death, do not remove the oil system module from a hot
                    engine. Wait until engine cools down before removing.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh05/H05011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Coolant drain plug</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a coolant drain pan under the oil system module.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the coolant drain plug (M18) at the bottom of the oil system module.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove coolant drain plug O-ring and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651009" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil filter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil system module assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place an oil drain pan under oil filter. After waiting for oil to cool down, remove, drain,
                and discard oil filter. Dispose or recycle oil and filter in accordance with local regulations.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651009.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>VGT oil supply tubing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the VGT oil supply tube fitting from the oil system module assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651009.7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>VGT oil supply tubing O-ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the VGT oil supply tube O-ring and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651012" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil system module and secondary filter assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil system module assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 30 (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose, 1 in O.D.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose clamp (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary filtration filter assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 25 (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler drain tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Support bracket bolt, M8 x 16</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 20 (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter (spin-on)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil cooler drain tube support bracket bolt (M8 x 16) at lower end.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull oil cooler drain tube (lower end) out of oil cooler module and discard O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove eight oil system module assembly bolts (M8 x 30).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the complete oil system module including the oil cooler and filter header as a unit
                (less oil filter) and place onto a clean workbench.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651012.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Oil and coolant seal locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the oil and coolant seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cap the open end of the VGT oil supply tube and fitting.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
